{"id":"ev_f1344ee7c61f4d21","runId":"run_190","type":"delegation","at":1782178766906,"data":{"workItemId":"wi_f5464b1b342c4f9e","atom":0,"task":"OWNER MAP (read-only, no code changes). Produce an evidence-backed owner map for ticket 0031 (founder 'stop the run' control lane) so Oscar can frame the design + ADR for the founder. Do NOT modify any code, tests, prompts, or docs in this atom — investigation only. Deliver a structured markdown report saved to cocoder/runs/46-run_190/owner-map-0031.md with these sections, each backed by exact file:line evidence (paths + line numbers + short quoted snippets):\n\n1. RUNNER LOOP: Locate the directive/verify/nudge loop the runner drives (the watcher that polls for directive-N.json, dispatches verify, and nudges Bob/Oscar/Deb). Name the file(s), the loop entry point, and where iteration/continuation is decided. Identify the single point where a 'stop' check could be honored to halt further nudges cleanly.\n\n2. STOP/TEARDOWN SURFACES TODAY: Find `cocoder oz teardown` implementation and the daemon stop endpoint (`POST /runs/:id/stop`). Name the exact handlers, what they do (close panes vs halt loop), and how they differ. Confirm whether any halt-the-loop-only (stop != teardown) path already exists.\n\n3. WATCHER/NUDGE OWNER: Trace the `deb-follows-oscar` / `deb-oscar-repair-loop` lineage — the watcher/nudge owner. Where do nudges originate? What state would need to gate them off on a registered stop?\n\n4. DIRECTIVE/SIGNAL ARTIFACT CONVENTION: Document how directive-N.json and verify artifacts are written/polled (path convention, who reads, who writes), since a file-based stop signal must follow this same convention (persona writes the signal, runner acts).\n\n5. PERSONA STOP CONTRACTS: Identify where persona prompts/standards encode the host/process-safety guardrail and F20 founder-explicit-only authority (teardown), since a stop lane must reuse that authority bar and forbid persona self-stop.\n\n6. TEST SURFACES: Locate the runner loop tests that would pin 'once a founder stop is registered, the loop emits no further nudges/dispatches and reaches a clean stopped state.' Name the test file(s) and the existing patterns to extend.\n\n7. ADR LANDSCAPE: List any existing ADRs touching teardown/stop/watcher/nudge authority (e.g. F20, ADR-0016, ADR-0036) that a new stop-control ADR must align with or reference.\n\nAcceptance: the report exists at the named path, every named owner has exact file:line evidence (not a guess), and section 1 ends with a concrete single recommended insertion point for the stop check. What must not break: nothing — this atom changes no behavior; it is pure investigation. If a named surface cannot be found, say so explicitly with the searches you ran rather than inventing a path."}}
